Title: Hollywood on Parade

reviewText: Even for those interested in early Hollywood there is not much of interest here - some stars in candid shots (on the Lurline, at the racetrack), some stars in scripted scenes. The scripted material is generally weak and a number of the "stars" are now totally forgotten. I don't think it is worth watching just to see Mary Pickford, Jean Harlow, Claudette Colbert, Loretta Young, or Constance and Joan Bennett. The clip of Tallulah Bankhead singing(???) is however a train wreck that needs to be seen.
Title: Hollywood on Parade
